New icon specification

We are introducing new design specifications for your app icons on Google Play. If you do not take any action by June 24, 2019, your app icon will be converted to legacy mode. Starting May 1, 2019, any new icons uploaded must meet the new guidelines. Visit your store listings for more information. Learn more

      New app icon specification for Google Play

      App icons on Google Play are changing. From June 24, transparent backgrounds will no longer be allowed, and Google Play will dynamically add rounded corners and drop shadows to icons.

      Icon specification for Google Play

      Google Play will dynamically add rounded corners and drop shadows to your icon. Transparent backgrounds are no longer allowed. Learn more

      Let us know when your icon meets the new specification. If you're not quite ready, you can keep using the old specification for now. We'll automatically scale down your icon on June 24.
